  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\nThe bug was originally found in https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/10288.\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nIt's hard to describe the issue, reproduce steps should be eaiser to read.\r\n\r\nHaving an account with 2 paired devices, with a community it's admin in, the first message in channel is not received on second device after being going back to online.\r\nBut (I think I saw this) if both devices are online, the first message is received everywhere.\r\n\r\nI'm pretty sure most of these details are not important here, but this is the way I faced it several times:\r\n- sending a user mention\r\n- being a community admin\r\n- the first device is mobile\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Alice [mobile], Charlie: create new profile\r\n2. Alice [mobile]: create a new community \"Doodles\" with require to join option\r\n3. Charlie: send Doodles join request\r\n4. Alice [mobile]: accept Charlie's join request\r\n--\r\n5. Alice [mobile]: pair new desktop device\r\n6. Alice [desktop]: close the app\r\n7. Charlie: send 2-3 messages to `#general` channel in Doodles\r\n8. Alice [desktop]: start the app, log in, and check:\r\n‚ùå Missing first Charlie's message in Doodles.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version: 9b8340b6957a68b99f3fd8721e185b1e7dbd00d4\r\n- Status mobile version: status-im/status-mobile@0ac6817488f02a7e31c9cf17fe2dead5d83e97df\r\n- Operating System: MacOS 13.4\r\n\r\n",
